#### Filtering criteria:
# S/N > 10
# Area > 20
# The Area of the sample must be higher than the area of the water blank before it to remove false positives

DATA$Threshold <- c(20)
#start with minimum threshold for area > 10
# if the background is higher than 20, paste new threshold vaue
# give minimum area of 20 for blanks
DATA$Area <- ifelse((DATA$Type == "Blank" & DATA$Area<20), c(20), DATA$Area)
DATA$Area <- ifelse((DATA$Type == "Blank" & is.na(DATA$Area)), c(20), DATA$Area)

BLANKAREAmax <-c()
for (i in 2:nrow(DATA)){
 if (DATA[i,"Type"] == "Blank" && DATA[(i-1),"Type"] == "Blank") {
   BLANKAREA1 <- DATA[i,"Area"]
   BLANKAREA2 <- DATA[(i-1),"Area"]
   BLANKAREAmax <- max(BLANKAREA1, BLANKAREA2)
  }
  if (DATA[i,"Type"] == "Analyte") {
    DATA[i,"Threshold"] <- BLANKAREAmax
  }
}

# make minimum threshold 20
#DATA$Threshold <- ifelse((DATA$Threshold < 0 || is.na(DATA$Threshold)), c(20), DATA$Threshold)
#for antibiotics with high carry over, set higher background threshold
#most blanks didnt have AUC calculated...
DATA$Threshold <- ifelse((DATA$Compound == "Sulfamethoxazole" & DATA$Threshold<250), c(250), DATA$Threshold)
DATA$Threshold <- ifelse((DATA$Compound == "Ciprofloxacin" & DATA$Threshold<250), c(250), DATA$Threshold)
DATA$Threshold <- ifelse((DATA$Compound == "Levofloxacin" & DATA$Threshold<250), c(250), DATA$Threshold)
DATA$Threshold <- ifelse(DATA$Sample.Text=="Sample_1160" & DATA$Compound=="Levofloxacin", 20, DATA$Threshold)

days_counter<- function(information, subject) {
  survey_subset<- subset(survey_all, Subject==subject &
                           Information==information)
  survey_subset$count <- c(0)
  counter <- c(0)
    for (i in 1:nrow(survey_subset)){
      if (survey_subset[i,which(colnames(survey_subset)=="value")]==1) {
        survey_subset[i, which(colnames(survey_subset)=="count")] <- counter
        counter<-0
      }
      else counter<-counter+1
      survey_subset[i, which(colnames(survey_subset)=="count")] <- counter
    }
   if (max(na.omit(as.numeric(survey_subset$count))) >= nrow(survey_subset)) {
     survey_subset[, which(colnames(survey_subset)=="count")] <- c("Pt did not take")
    }
      assign("survey_subset", survey_subset, env=.GlobalEnv)
    }

subjectlist <- levels(as.factor(survey_all$Subject))

                        mapply(FUN=days_counter,informationlist,  x, SIMPLIFY = FALSE)))

#acquity data not normally distributed: Azithro, Aztreonam, Ceftazidime, Cipro, Trimethoprim
# xevo data not normally dist: azithromycin, aztreonam, trimethoprim 
shapiro.test((subset(detected_data_xevo, Compound=="Trimethoprim" & Conc>0)$Conc))
## 
##  Shapiro-Wilk normality test
## 
## data:  (subset(detected_data_xevo, Compound == "Trimethoprim" & Conc >     0)$Conc)
## W = 0.71959, p-value = 0.009877
detected_data_xevo[which(detected_data_xevo$Sample=="1162" & detected_data_xevo$Compound=="Levofloxacin"),]$Conc <- detected_data_xevo[which(detected_data_xevo$Sample=="1162" & detected_data_xevo$Compound=="Levofloxacin"),]$Conc + 0.1

detected_data_xevo$both <- paste(detected_data_xevo$Sample, detected_data_xevo$Compound, sep="_")
detected_data_acquity$both <- paste(detected_data_acquity$Sample, detected_data_acquity$Compound, sep="_")


detected_data_xevo<-detected_data_xevo[detected_data_xevo$both %in% detected_data_acquity$both,]

detected_data_acquity<-detected_data_acquity[detected_data_acquity$both %in% detected_data_xevo$both,]


wilcox_antbx <- function(X) {wilcox.test(subset(detected_data_acquity, Compound==X & Conc>0)$Conc, subset(detected_data_xevo, Conc>0 &Compound==X)$Conc, paired=TRUE, alternative = "two.sided")}


#### do concentrations differ across instruments? #####

g_legend <- function(a.gplot){ 
    tmp <- ggplot_gtable(ggplot_build(a.gplot)) 
    leg <- which(sapply(tmp$grobs, function(x) x$name) == "guide-box") 
    legend <- tmp$grobs[[leg]] 
    legend

   BLANKAREA2 <- data_extravolume[(i-1),6]

    data_extravolume[i,19] <- BLANKAREAmax

#### confusion matrix ####
confusion_matrix<- function(X, DF) {
 print(paste(X))
  print(c("lcms_yes_survey_yes",nrow(subset(DF, Compound==paste(X) & ( Survey.Hits=="Reported \n taken" & Conc>0)))))
  print(c('lcms_no_survey_yes', nrow(subset(DF, Compound==paste(X) & ( Survey.Hits=="Reported \n taken" & Conc==0)))))
  print(c('lcms_yes_survey_no', nrow(subset(DF, Compound==paste(X) & ( Survey.Hits=="Reported \n not \n taken" & Conc>0)))))
print(c('lcms_no_survey_no',nrow(subset(DF, Compound==paste(X) & ( Survey.Hits=="Reported \n not \n taken" & Conc==0)))))
}

#### confusion matrix for iv, inhaled ####
confusion_matrix_byinfo<- function(X, DF) {
   print(paste(X))
  print(c("lcms_yes_survey_yes",nrow(subset(DF, Information==paste(X) & ( Survey.Hits=="Reported \n taken" & Conc>0)))))
  print(c('lcms_no_survey_yes', nrow(subset(DF, Information==paste(X) & ( Survey.Hits=="Reported \n taken" & Conc==0)))))
  print(c('lcms_yes_survey_no', nrow(subset(DF, Information==paste(X) & ( Survey.Hits=="Reported \n not \n taken" & Conc>0)))))
print(c('lcms_no_survey_no',nrow(subset(DF, Information==paste(X) & ( Survey.Hits=="Reported \n not \n taken" & Conc==0)))))
}


lapply(X=c("Aztreonam.Inhaled.", "Aztreonam.IV.", "Tobramycin.Inhaled.", "Tobramycin.IV."), DF=lcms_survey_acquity,FUN=confusion_matrix_byinfo)

#### Sensitivity (TP/P, P=FN+TP) ####

calculate_sensitivity <- function(X, DF) {

survey_yes_lcms_yes <- nrow(subset(DF, Compound==paste(X) &  Survey.Hits=="Reported \n taken" & Conc>0))
print(paste(X))
print(survey_yes_lcms_yes/total_positive)
}

### Specificity  ###
# TN / TN + FP 
# TN / N
calculate_specificity <- function(X, DF) {
  true_neg<-nrow(subset(DF, Compound==paste(X) & ( Survey.Hits=="Reported \n not \n taken" & Conc==0)))
  false_pos <-nrow(subset(DF, Compound==paste(X) & ( Survey.Hits=="Reported \n not \n taken" & Conc>0)))
print(paste(X))
print(true_neg/(true_neg+false_pos))
}

### PPV ###
# (TP/TP+FP)
calculate_ppv <- function(X, DF) {
  true_pos<-nrow(subset(DF, Compound==paste(X) & ( Survey.Hits=="Reported \n taken" & Conc>0)))
  false_pos <-nrow(subset(DF, Compound==paste(X) & ( Survey.Hits=="Reported \n not \n taken" & Conc>0)))
print(paste(X))
print(true_pos/(true_pos+false_pos))
}

### NPV ###
# (TN/ TN + FN)
calculate_npv <- function(X, DF) {
  true_neg<-nrow(subset(DF, Compound==paste(X) & ( Survey.Hits=="Reported \n not \n taken" & Conc==0)))
  false_neg <-nrow(subset(DF, Compound==paste(X) & ( Survey.Hits=="Reported \n taken" & Conc==0)))
print(paste(X))
print(true_neg/(true_neg+false_neg))
}

# Sensitivity = true positive rate 
# TPR = TP/(TP+FN)

antibiotic_list<-levels(factor(lcms_survey_subset2$Compound))

TEMP<-c()
DF <- c()
TEMP2 <-c()
for (X in antibiotic_list) {
  TEMP <- subset(lcms_survey_subset2, Compound==paste(X))
TruePosAcquity <-nrow(subset(TEMP, Instrument=="Acquity" & (Survey.Hits=="Reported \n taken" & Filtered=="yes"))) 
FalseNegAcquity <- nrow(subset(TEMP, Instrument=="Acquity" & (Survey.Hits=="Reported \n taken" & Filtered=="no")))
TPR= TruePosAcquity/(FalseNegAcquity+TruePosAcquity)

TEMP2 <- cbind(TPR, paste(X))
DF <- rbind(DF, TEMP2)
  
}
